parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission's failure to shift gears can cause the vehicle to stall or lose power, leading to accidents or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The transmission fails to shift gears
the vehicle dies when making turns

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine overheating can cause damage to the engine, leading to costly repairs, and potentially causing the vehicle to stall or lose power, which can lead to accidents.
symptoms: the vehicle stalls or loses power due to overheating.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Cracking of the cylinder head or head gasket can cause engine coolant and oil leaks, leading to engine overheating, damage, and potential failure, which can result in costly repairs, engine replacement, or even accidents due to loss of vehicle control.
Failure of the oxygen sensor can cause poor engine performance, decreased fuel efficiency, and increased emissions, which can lead to costly repairs, decreased vehicle safety, and environmental harm.
Grinding brakes can cause reduced stopping power, increased stopping distance, and potential accidents, as well as increased wear on brake components, leading to costly repairs.
symptoms: Grinding or screeching noise when applying the brakes
vibration or pulsation in the brake pedal

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Leaking valve cover gaskets can cause oil leaks, engine damage, and decreased engine performance, which can lead to costly repairs, engine replacement, or even accidents due to loss of vehicle control.
symptoms: oil drips or spots under the vehicle

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Failure of the air conditioner can cause discomfort, distraction, and decreased driver focus, which can lead to accidents, as well as increased stress and decreased overall vehicle satisfaction.
symptoms: air conditioner does not turn on
unusual noises or smells from the air conditioner.
